`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- `buildTerrainGeometry` is exported as a named pure function — this lets tests verify geometry construction without a WebGL context or R3F, mirroring the `getCameraPosition` / `isGrounded` / `rotateByYaw` precedents.
- Vertex colors in Three.js require both `geometry.setAttribute("color", ...)` (3-component RGB float buffer) AND `material.vertexColors: true`. Missing either silently falls back to white.
- `geometry.computeVertexNormals()` is critical after heightmap displacement — without it, lighting shading is wrong because normals still point straight up from the flat plane.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

